    "Still early days and how we assess will continually evolve as these tools evolve\".",
    "A total of 360 motivations for changing assessment were coded, with over 70% (264 responses) relating to Performance Expectancy.",
    "Similar to the results of the motivations 1 3",
    "Education and Information Technologies (2024) 29:15403-15439 to change their teaching, the majority of teachers expressed the intention to change assessment tasks to influence the performance expectancy of their students (n = 160).",
    "Participants believed that the change would enable \"students to develop their own skills and abilities\", \"prepare students for life and workplace with AI\", and they wanted to \"de-motivate students from using AI as a way to cheat on their coursework\"."
